page.title: 20Stags End House
page.content: - The main house at Stags End has been occupied since early this year by the U.K. marketing division of the{multi- {national timber company,}Schauman. - The building itself has had a lot of money spent on it to renovate it and make it suitable for offices. It has an{Edwardian staircase}listed as of great{architectural interest}so it has to be preserved. The parent company is from Finland and owns alot of forest and timber mills there. They make all sorts of{timber products including chipboard, plywood, paper and paper-pulp and even yachts. The - The rear of the building used to be occupied by a company of landscape engineers which has just gone into liquidation. -{The stables}at the back of the house is where the{Husky Riding Centre}used to operate.
